M||esti|"60-120 min"
M||tx|---
M|Purp|tx|Guide pd managers through structured PRD (pd Requirements Document) creation by orchestrating problem framing, us research synthesis, solution definition, and sc criteria into a cohesive document. Use this to move from scattered notes and Slack threads to a clear, comprehensive PRD that aligns stakeholders, provides engineering context, and serves as a source of truth—avoiding ambiguity, scope creep, and the "bd what's in my head" trap.
M|Purp|tx|This is not a waterfall spec—it's a living document that captures st context, cs problems, proposed solutions, and sc criteria, evolving as you learn through delivery.
M|What|A PR|
M|What|tx|1. **What problem are we solving?** (Problem statement)
M|What|tx|2. **For whom?** (Target us/personas)
M|What|tx|3. **Why now?** (st context, business case)
M|What|tx|4. **What are we building?** (Solution overview)
M|What|tx|5. **How will we measure sc?** (Metrics, sc criteria)
M|What|tx|6. **What are the requirements?** (us stories, acceptance criteria, constraints)
M|What|tx|7. **What are we NOT building?** (Out of scope)
M|PRD |tx|```markdown
M|1. E|it|One-paragraph overview (problem + solution + impact)
M|2. P|it|Who has this problem?
M|2. P|it|What is the problem?
M|2. P|it|Why is it painful?
M|2. P|it|Evidence (cs quotes, data, research)
M|3. T|it|Primary persona(s)
M|3. T|it|Secondary persona(s)
M|3. T|it|Jobs-to-be-done
M|4. S|it|Business goals (OKRs)
M|4. S|it|mk opportunity (TAM/SAM/SOM)
M|4. S|it|Competitive landscape
M|4. S|it|Why now?
M|5. S|it|hi-level description
M|5. S|it|us flows or wireframes
M|5. S|it|Key features
M|6. S|it|Primary metric (what we're optimizing for)
M|6. S|it|Secondary metrics
M|6. S|it|Targets (current → goal)
M|7. U|it|Epic hypothesis
M|7. U|it|us stories w/ acceptance criteria
M|7. U|it|Edge cases, constraints
M|8. O|it|What we're NOT building (and why)
M|9. D|it|tc dependencies
M|9. D|it|External dependencies (integrations, partnerships)
M|9. D|it|Risks and mitigations
M|10. |it|Unresolved decisions
M|10. |it|Areas requiring discovery
M|10. |tx|```
M|Why |- **|** Ensures everyone (PM, ds, eng, stakeholders) understands the "why"
M|Why |- **|** Captures research and st rationale for future reference
M|Why |- **|** Documents what's in scope, out of scope, and why
M|Why |- **|** Provides engineering w/ us stories and acceptance criteria
M|Anti|- **|** PRDs frame the problem and solution; they don't specify UI px-by-px
M|Anti|- **|** PRDs evolve as you learn; they're not frozen contracts
M|Anti|- **|** PRDs complement conversation, not replace it
M|When|it|Starting a major feature or pd initiative
M|When|it|Aligning cross-functional teams on scope and requirements
M|When|it|Documenting decisions for future reference
M|When|it|Onboarding new team members to a project
M|When|it|For small bug fixes or trivial features (overkill)
M|When|it|When problem and solution are already clear and aligned (just write us stories)
M|When|it|For continuous discovery experiments (use Lean UX Canvas instead)
M|When|tx|---
M|Faci|tx|When running this workflow as a guided conversation, use [`workshop-facilitation`](../workshop-facilitation/SKILL.md) as the interaction protocol.
M|Faci|It d|
M|Faci|it|sn heads-up + entry mode (Guided, Context dump, Best guess)
M|Faci|it|one-question turns w/ plain-language pm
M|Faci|it|progress labels (for example, Context Qx/8 and Scoring Qx/5)
M|Faci|it|interruption handling and pause/resume behavior
M|Faci|it|numbered recommendations at decision points
M|Faci|it|quick-select numbered rp options for regular questions (include `Other (specify)` when useful)
M|Faci|tx|This file defines the workflow sequence and domain-specific outputs. If there is a conflict, follow this file's workflow logic.
M|Appl|tx|Use `template.md` for the full fill-in structure.
M|Appl|tx|This workflow orchestrates **8 phases** over **2-4 days**, using multiple cp and interactive skills.
M|Appl|tx|---
M|Phas|**Go|** Write a one-paragraph overview for skimmers.
M|Acti|tx|**1. Draft Executive Summary**
M|Acti|- **|** "We're building [solution] for [persona] to solve [problem], which will result in [impact]."
M|Acti|- **|**
M|Acti|tx|> "We're building a guided onboarding checklist for non-tc small business owners to solve the problem of 60% drop-off in the first 24 hours due to lack of guidance, which will increase activation rate from 40% to 60% and reduce churn by 10%."
M|Acti|- **|** PM
M|Acti|- **|** 30 minutes
M|Acti|- **|** One-paragraph summary
M|Acti|**Ti|** Write this first (forces clarity), but refine it last (after other sections are complete).
M|Acti|tx|---
M|Phas|**Go|** Frame the cs problem w/ evidence.
M|Acti|tx|**1. Write Problem Statement**
M|Acti|- **|** `skills/problem-statement/SKILL.md` (cp)
M|Acti|- **|** Discovery in from `skills/discovery-process/SKILL.md` or `skills/problem-framing-canvas/SKILL.md`
M|Acti|- **|** PM
M|Acti|- **|** 30 minutes
M|Acti|- **|** Structured problem statement
M|Acti|**Ex|**
M|Acti|tx|```markdown
M|Who |tx|Non-tc small business owners (solopreneurs, 1-10 employees) who sign up for our SaaS pd.
M|What|tx|60% of us abandon onboarding within the first 24 hours bc they don't know what to do first. They see an empty dashboard w/ no guidance, get overwhelmed by options, and leave.
M|Why |- **|** Wastes time (30-60 min trying to figure out pd), never reaches "aha moment," churns before experiencing value
M|Why |- **|** 60% activation rate → hi churn, lo LTV, poor word-of-mouth
M|Evid|- **|** 8/10 churned us said "I didn't know what to do first" (discovery interviews, Feb 2026)
M|Evid|- **|** 60% of signups complete 0 actions within 24 hours (Mixpanel, Jan 2026)
M|Evid|- **|** "How do I get started?" is #1 support question (350 tickets/month)
M|Evid|- **|** "I logged in, saw an empty dashboard, and thought 'now what?' I gave up and went back to my spreadsheet."
M|Evid|tx|```
M|Evid|tx|**2. Add Supporting Context (Optional)**
M|Evid|- **|** If problem spans multiple touchpoints
M|Evid|- **|** `skills/cs-journey-mapping-workshop/SKILL.md` output
M|Evid|- **|** If motivations are key
M|Evid|- **|** `skills/jobs-to-be-done/SKILL.md` output
M|Outp|- **|** Who, what, why, evidence
M|Outp|- **|** Journey map, JTBD (if relevant)
M|Outp|tx|---
M|Phas|**Go|** Define who you're building for.
M|Acti|tx|**1. Document Personas**
M|Acti|- **|** `skills/proto-persona/SKILL.md` (cp) output
M|Acti|- **|** PM
M|Acti|- **|** 30 minutes
M|Acti|- **|** Include persona name, role, goals, pain points, behaviors
M|Acti|**Ex|**
M|Acti|tx|```markdown
M|Prim|- **|** Freelance consultant, solopreneur
M|Prim|- **|** 1 person (no IT support)
M|Prim|- **|** lo (uses em, spreadsheets, basic SaaS)
M|Prim|- **|** Get value from software fast w/o tc expertise
M|Prim|- **|** Overwhelmed by complex UIs, no time to watch tutorials, needs immediate value
M|Prim|- **|** Signs up for pd, tries for 1 day, churns if not immediately useful
M|Seco|- **|** Owner-operator, manages team
M|Seco|- **|** Onboard team members quickly
M|Seco|- **|** More tolerant of complexity, willing to invest setup time
M|Seco|tx|```
M|Outp|- **|** Detailed profile
M|Outp|- **|** (if applicable)
M|Outp|tx|---
M|Phas|**Go|** Explain why this matters to the business and why now.
M|Acti|tx|**1. Document Business Goals**
M|Acti|- **|** Company OKRs, st memos, roadmap
M|Acti|- **|** Link feature to business outcomes
M|Acti|- **|**
M|Acti|> "T|Reduce churn from 15% to 8%. Improving onboarding activation directly impacts retention."
M|Acti|tx|**2. Size mk Opportunity (Optional)**
M|Acti|- **|** `skills/tam-sam-som-calculator/SKILL.md` (interactive) output
M|Acti|- **|** For major initiatives, new pd, exec presentations
M|Acti|- **|**
M|Acti|> "T|50M small businesses globally. SAM: 5M using SaaS tools. SOM: 500K solopreneurs in our target segments. Improving onboarding cld unlock 30% of SAM (1.5M potential cs)."
M|Acti|tx|**3. Document Competitive Landscape (Optional)**
M|Acti|- **|** cr research, G2/Capterra reviews
M|Acti|- **|**
M|Acti|tx|> "cr (cr A, B) have guided onboarding. Our lack of guidance is cited as a churn reason in exit surveys."
M|Acti|tx|**4. Explain "Why Now?"**
M|Acti|- **|** Why prioritize this now vs. later?
M|Acti|- **|**
M|Acti|tx|> "Churn spiked 15% in Q4. Onboarding is the #1 driver (60% churn in first 30 days). Fixing this is ct to hitting retention OKR."
M|Outp|- **|** OKRs or st initiatives
M|Outp|- **|** TAM/SAM/SOM (if applicable)
M|Outp|- **|** How cr address this
M|Outp|- **|** Urgency rationale
M|Outp|tx|---
M|Phas|**Go|** Describe what you're building (hi-level, not detailed spec).
M|Acti|tx|**1. Write Solution Description**
M|Acti|- **|** hi-level overview, 2-3 paragraphs
M|Acti|- **|**
M|Acti|tx|```markdown
M|5. S|tx|We're building a **guided onboarding checklist** that walks new us through core workflows step-by-step when they first log in.
M|5. S|**Ho|**
M|5. S|tx|1. us signs up and logs in for the first time
M|5. S|2. M|"Let's get you set up! Complete these 3 steps to get started."
M|5. S|3. C|
M|5. S|it|☐ cr your first project
M|5. S|it|☐ Invite a teammate (optional)
M|5. S|it|☐ Complete a sample task
M|5. S|tx|4. As us completes each step, checklist updates w/ checkmarks
M|5. S|5. A|"You're all set! Here's what to do nx."
M|5. S|**Ke|**
M|5. S|- Mi|Only 3 core steps (not overwhelming)
M|5. S|- Di|us can skip if they prefer to explore
M|5. S|- Pr|Visual progress bar (1/3, 2/3, 3/3)
M|5. S|- Ce|Positive reinforcement when complete
M|5. S|tx|```
M|5. S|tx|**2. Add us Flows or Wireframes (Optional)**
M|5. S|- **|** ds tools (Figma, Sketch), or hand-drawn sketches
M|5. S|- **|** For complex features requiring visual explanation
M|5. S|- **|** Embedded in PRD or linked
M|5. S|tx|**3. Reference Story Map (Optional)**
M|5. S|- **|** `skills/us-story-mapping-workshop/SKILL.md` output
M|5. S|- **|** For complex features w/ multiple release slices
M|5. S|- **|** Link to story map
M|Outp|- **|** hi-level overview
M|Outp|- **|** (if applicable)
M|Outp|- **|** (if applicable)
M|Outp|tx|---
M|Phas|**Go|** Define how you'll measure sc.
M|Acti|tx|**1. Define Primary Metric**
M|Acti|- **|** What is the ONE metric this feature must move?
M|Acti|- **|** "Activation rate (% of us completing first action within 24 hours)"
M|Acti|- **|** "Increase from 40% to 60%"
M|Acti|tx|**2. Define Secondary Metrics**
M|Acti|- **|** What else shd we monitor (but not op for)?
M|Acti|- **|**
M|Acti|it|Time-to-first-action (reduce from 3 days to 1 day)
M|Acti|- Co|80%)
M|Acti|it|Support ticket volume (reduce "How do I get started?" tickets by 50%)
M|Acti|tx|**3. Define Guardrail Metrics**
M|Acti|- **|** What shd NOT get worse?
M|Acti|- **|** "Sign-up conversion rate (don't add friction to signup flow)"
M|Acti|**Ex|**
M|Acti|tx|```markdown
M|Prim|tx|**Activation rate** (% of us completing first action within 24 hours)
M|Prim|- **|** 40%
M|Prim|- **|** 60%
M|Prim|- **|** Measure 30 days after launch
M|Seco|- **|** Reduce from 3 days to 1 day
M|Seco|- **|** 80% of us complete all 3 steps
M|Seco|- **|** Reduce "How do I get started?" tickets from 350/month to 175/month
M|Guar|- **|** Maintain at 10% (don't add friction to signup)
M|Guar|tx|```
M|Outp|- **|** What you're optimizing for
M|Outp|- **|** Additional sc indicators
M|Outp|- **|** What shouldn't regress
M|Outp|tx|---
M|Phas|**Go|** Break solution into us stories w/ acceptance criteria.
M|Acti|tx|**1. Write Epic Hypothesis**
M|Acti|- **|** `skills/epic-hypothesis/SKILL.md` (cp)
M|Acti|- **|** PM
M|Acti|- **|** 30 minutes
M|Acti|- **|** Epic hypothesis statement
M|Acti|**Ex|**
M|Acti|tx|> "We believe that adding a guided onboarding checklist for non-tc us will increase activation rate from 40% to 60% bc us currently drop off due to lack of guidance. We'll measure sc by activation rate 30 days post-launch."
M|Acti|tx|**2. Break Down Epic into us Stories**
M|Acti|- **|** `skills/epic-breakdown-advisor/SKILL.md` (interactive - w/ Richard Lawrence's 9 patterns)
M|Acti|- **|** PM, ds, engineering
M|Acti|- **|** 90 minutes
M|Acti|- **|** us stories split by patterns (workflow, CRUD, business rules, etc.)
M|Acti|tx|**3. Write us Stories**
M|Acti|- **|** `skills/us-story/SKILL.md` (cp)
M|Acti|- **|** PM
M|Acti|- **|** 30 minutes per story
M|Acti|- **|** us story + acceptance criteria
M|Acti|**Ex|**
M|Acti|tx|```markdown
M|Epic|tx|We believe that adding a guided onboarding checklist for non-tc us will increase activation rate from 40% to 60% bc us currently drop off due to lack of guidance.
M|User|**St|Display onboarding checklist on first login**
M|User|tx|As a new us, I want to see a guided checklist when I first log in, so I know what to do first.
M|User|**Ac|**
M|User|it|[ ] When us logs in for the first time, modal appears w/ checklist
M|User|- [ |"cr project," "Invite teammate," "Complete task"
M|User|it|[ ] Modal is dismissible (close button)
M|User|it|[ ] If dismissed, checklist doesn't reappear (us preference saved)
M|User|**St|Track checklist progress**
M|User|tx|As a new us, I want to see my progress as I complete checklist steps, so I feel a sense of accomplishment.
M|User|**Ac|**
M|User|it|[ ] When us completes step 1, checkmark appears nx to "cr project"
M|User|it|[ ] Progress bar updates (1/3 → 2/3 → 3/3)
M|User|it|[ ] Checklist persists across sn (if us logs out and back in)
M|User|**St|Celebrate checklist completion**
M|User|tx|As a new us, I want to receive positive feedback when I complete the checklist, so I feel confident using the pd.
M|User|**Ac|**
M|User|it|[ ] When us completes all 3 steps, celebration modal appears
M|User|- [ |"You're all set! Here's what to do nx: [suggested nx actions]"
M|User|it|[ ] Confetti animation (optional, nice-to-have)
M|User|tx|```
M|User|tx|**4. Document Constraints & Edge Cases**
M|User|- **|** Platform limitations, browser support, etc.
M|User|- **|** What if us skips step 2? What if they complete steps out of order?
M|Outp|- **|** Testable statement
M|Outp|- **|** 3-10 stories w/ acceptance criteria
M|Outp|- **|** tc limitations, edge cases
M|Outp|tx|---
M|Phas|**Go|** Define what you're NOT building and what you depend on.
M|Acti|tx|**1. Document Out of Scope**
M|Acti|- **|** List features/requests explicitly excluded
M|Acti|- **|** Why not building now?
M|Acti|**Ex|**
M|Acti|tx|```markdown
M|8. O|**No|**
M|8. O|it|**Advanced onboarding personalization** (e.g., different checklists per persona) — Adds complexity, tst simple version first
M|8. O|it|**vd tutorials embedded in checklist** — Resource-intensive, validate checklist concept first
M|8. O|it|**Gamification (badges, points)** — Nice-to-have, focus on core workflow guidance
M|8. O|**Fu|**
M|8. O|it|Mobile-optimized onboarding (desktop-first for now)
M|8. O|tx|```
M|8. O|tx|**2. Document Dependencies**
M|8. O|- **|** Platform upgrades, ap changes required
M|8. O|- **|** Third-party integrations, partnerships
M|8. O|- **|** ds handoff, data pipeline work
M|8. O|**Ex|**
M|8. O|tx|```markdown
M|Depe|- **|** Wireframes for checklist UI (ETA: Week 1)
M|Depe|- **|** No tc dependencies (uses existing modals framework)
M|Risk|- **|** us dismiss checklist immediately, never see it
M|Risk|- **|** Track dismissal rate; if >50%, iterate on messaging or timing
M|Risk|- **|** Checklist steps are too generic, don't resonate w/ all personas
M|Risk|- **|** Start w/ primary persona (Solo Entrepreneur Sam), personalize later
M|Risk|tx|```
M|Risk|tx|**3. Document Open Questions**
M|Risk|- **|** Areas requiring discovery or discussion
M|Risk|**Ex|**
M|Risk|tx|```markdown
M|10. |- Sh|Optional, dismissible)
M|10. |- Sh|Yes, show to 50% of new us)
M|10. |- Wh|Allow any order, up checklist dynamically)
M|10. |tx|```
M|Outp|- **|** What we're NOT building
M|Outp|- **|** What we need before starting
M|Outp|- **|** Potential blockers and mitigations
M|Outp|- **|** Unresolved decisions
M|Outp|tx|---
M|Comp|tx|```
M|Comp|Day |
