M|Comp|**To|**
M|Comp|- **|** 1.5-2 days (straightforward feature, clear requirements)
M|Comp|- **|** 2-3 days (includes discovery synthesis, stakeholder rv)
M|Comp|- **|** 3-4 days (major initiative, multiple personas, extensive us stories)
M|Comp|tx|---
M|Exam|tx|See `examples/sample.md` for full PRD examples.
M|Exam|Mini|
M|Exam|tx|```markdown
M|2. P|it|60% of trial us drop off in first 24 hours
M|6. S|- Ac|40% → 60%
M|6. S|tx|```
M|Pitf|**Sy|** PM writes PRD alone, presents finished doc to team
M|Pitf|**Co|** No buy-in, team doesn't understand rationale
M|Pitf|fix|** Collaborate on Phase 7 (us stories) w/ ds + eng; rv draft PRD before finalizing
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "We believe us have this problem" (no data, no quotes)
M|Pitf|**Co|** Team questions whether problem is real
M|Pitf|fix|** Use discovery in from `skills/discovery-process/SKILL.md`; include cs quotes, an, support tickets
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** PRD specifies exact UI, px dimensions, button colors
M|Pitf|**Co|** Removes ds collaboration, becomes waterfall spec
M|Pitf|fix|** Keep Phase 5 hi-level; let ds own UI details
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** PRD defines problem + solution but no metrics
M|Pitf|**Co|** Can't validate if feature succeeded
M|Pitf|fix|** Always define primary metric in Phase 6 (what you're optimizing for)
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** No section on what's NOT being built
M|Pitf|**Co|** Scope creep, stakeholders expect features not planned
M|Pitf|fix|** Explicitly document out of scope in Phase 8
M|Pitf|tx|---
